// chunk c3: a slice-typed global with an ArrayLit initializer is sema-ok.
// `global s : i64[] = [1, 2, 3];` - the slice global is accepted in v1 (16-byte
// {ptr,len} slot + a backing region; ptr is stored as a relative offset within
// the globals block so the baked bytes round-trip through .em without loader
// fixup). The index read `s[2]` is type-checked as i64. (Runtime value verified
// by examples/aggregate_global_test, in-process; .em slice round-trip is a
// known follow-on if the loader lacks relative-ptr support.)
global s : i64[] = [1, 2, 3];
fn main() -> i64 { return s[2]; }
